@startuml
title seccomp-bpf — filtering a system call

start
:Process issues a system call\n(syscall number + arguments);
if (seccomp filter installed?) then (no)
  #lightgray:Normal kernel processing;
  stop
else (yes)
endif
:Kernel runs the attached BPF program\non the syscall number/args;
switch (filter verdict)
case (SECCOMP_RET_ALLOW)
  #90ee90:Execute the syscall;
  stop
case (SECCOMP_RET_ERRNO)
  #ffd27f:Skip syscall, return an error code;
  stop
case (SECCOMP_RET_TRAP)
  #ffd27f:Deliver SIGSYS to the process;
  stop
case (SECCOMP_RET_KILL)
  #ff9999:Terminate the process;
  note right
    Strict mode (mode 1) is the
    degenerate filter: only read,
    write, exit, sigreturn pass;
    everything else is KILL.
  end note
  stop
endswitch
@enduml
